The Acting Minister in the Presidency, Khumbudzo Ntshavheni, is giving an update on the ongoing violent protests in some parts of South Africa. Residents in parts of Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal have been looting shops. This has left a trail of destruction. Members of the South African National Defence Force (SANDF) have been deployed to assist police to restore order. Acting Minister in the Presidency Khumbudzo Ntshavheni gives an update on progress made thus far:   